overall_summary: The community is navigating a transition to ElizaOS, focusing on the Jeju Network infrastructure and DegenAI trading framework. Technical progress is centered on backend integrations, image generation pipelines, and unified transport hooks for better developer experience.
key_facts: The ElizaOS token migration from AI16Z is scheduled to conclude in February.
Shaw shared progress on the Jeju backend, featuring an OAuth3 testnet site routing to IPFS assets via an on-chain registry.
DegenAI is being developed to execute autonomous trades for users holding 1M tokens.
The core ElizaOS repository showed minimal activity between December 31, 2025, and January 1, 2026, with no new PRs or issues.
ElizaOS is available on Solana, Base, Ethereum, and BSC chains.
PR #81 in the docs repository increased documentation coverage to approximately 95%.
A unified useElizaChat hook was introduced to provide a single interface for HTTP, SSE, and WebSocket transports.
The ElizaOS token grew approximately 120% following Shaw's return to social media platform X.

discord_updates.summary: Focus on token utility, migration help, and the introduction of DegenAI as an autonomous trading framework powered by ElizaOS.
Technical discussions on Jeju backend, OAuth3 testnets, and speculative side projects like recreating classic games using the agent framework.
Market analysis revolving around debt monetization, capital rotation into risk-on assets, and infrastructure migration to self-owned data centers.

user_feedback.feedback_summary: Users report issues with MetaMask connectivity and token transfers, generally finding better success by importing to Phantom.
Improvement needed for website accessibility regarding clear tokenomics and contract address information.

strategic_insights.insight: The project is moving away from AWS toward self-owned, physical data center racks to ensure long-term decentralization and cost-efficiency.
implications_or_questions: How will this physical decentralization affect initial latency for global agent deployment?
Can the community contribute to this decentralized hardware layer?

market_analysis.observation: Capital rotation from gold/precious metals into risk-on assets like ElizaOS is predicted due to debt monetization cycles.
market_analysis.relevance: Drives token demand and community economic sentiment.
